name: James Warren
text: Facilities are well maintained, communication is easy and everyone is friendly. If you’re looking for a coach for all levels, ask for Jacob; he’s the man! Disciplined yet delicate, eloquent yet concise, his coaching surpassed any of my past experiences and renewed my love for the sport. Many thanks to Maestro Jacob

name: Teresa Ziemba
text: I am taking private tennis lessons with Jacob McAllister. My experience has been very positive. I can tell he really cares about making us better tennis players and gives very helpful/personal advice. He’s very efficient with our time. I’m excited to keep improving while taking these lessons.

name: Lisa McManus
text:
Had a great experience this past Saturday at Inverness CC.
I was with a group of ladies set to play at 10:30. It rained off and on & was of course very frustrating.. Joey was determined to get our court dry so we could play and also followed up with doing the lines for us!
What a great tennis professional. JC you hired a good one! Very polite too!
Enjoyed our tennis! Lisa Longshore Webb~

name: William Stephens
text: My fiancé and I have been taking private tennis lessons weekly here and really enjoy it. The cost is very reasonable and not excessive like some other private lessons we looked into. Our instructor (Jacob McAllister) has been great, very friendly, and really knows his stuff. He’s been super helpful with any questions we’ve had even outside of our tennis lessons and teaches us in a fun way. The courts are some of the nicest I’ve played at and very well maintained.

name: No U
text: The coaches are AMAZING!!! They are very good at working with children and give great feedback. Along that track they have Junior Team Tennis which is a great way for children to get experience with getting matches in and experiencing the feel of playing. They also have adult programs that are amazing! 10/10 would recommend!!!😃

resp.text: Thank you for the 5 star rating Hello People! That is great feedback and we're grateful for your support. Have a great day!

name: Tyler Miller
text: Took lessons for a few months with J.C. at the tennis complex and absolutely loved it. Would highly recommend for anyone at any level. Private lessons were very competitively priced and the facilities are second to none in Birmingham.

name: Drake Maxwell
text: Gorgeous setting along the Tennessee River. Too bad it's just not been maintained. At the very front portico, the chipped paint is waving a welcome as you drive up. The base of the columns are rotted away and the whole interior and exterior needs a huge overhaul. The Club restrooms downstairs are more akin to a Shell station. We were considering hosting a wedding here due to its beautiful lawn that goes down to the river, but after touring the facility we would be better off at a KOA Campground.
